"n.(个人、团体或民族)道德风貌，思潮，信仰 【英】 n. (个人，团体或民族) 道德风貌，思潮信仰( the characteristic and distinguishing attitudes, habits, beliefs of an individual or of a group) 【记】 eth=ethn(种族)+os→ 种族气氛→道德风貌 无 【记】与ethn- 和ethi- 都相关的，关于人，种族的道德，精神气质 ethos (n.)  revived by Palgrave in 1851 from Greek ethos ""moral character, nature, disposition, habit, custom,"" from suffixed form of PIE root *s(w)e- (see idiom). An important concept in Aristotle (as in ""Rhetoric"" II xii-xiv)."
